cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with document image compression, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of pattern matching and codebook generation also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The cross-entropy approach and k-median problem are optimization techniques that fall under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of compression techniques in document images is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
